What is OAuth

What is OAuth?
Third party, user-agent, delegated authorization. 

Give an example of what using OAuth would look like.
Uising another websites framework to auhtorize a users login. 

How does OAuth work? What are the steps that it takes to authenticate the user?
one site connects to the other on behalf of the user. second websites generates a token and secret unique to the user and the current transaction
token and secret give to users client software. token and secret presented to auth provider. client authenticated. user approves transaction. 
user given approved access token. token given to first website. first site gives token to second site on behalf of user. transaction successfully
complteted. 

What is OpenID?
authentication.

Authorization and Authentication flows

What is the difference between authorization and authentication?
authentication is user providing ownership of identity. athorization is letting a subject access the resources
after authentication. 
What is Authorization Code Flow?
flow of authorization on the server side. 
What is Authorization Code Flow with Proof Key for Code Exchange (PKCE)?
authorization code flow for single page apps. 
What is Implicit Flow with Form Post?
used for public clients. 
What is Client Credentials Flow?
for machine to machine apps, authorizing the client
What is Device Authorization Flow?
allows user to authenticate from a seperate device, rather than the input constrained one they may be using. 
What is Resource Owner Password Flow?
user provides credentials using an interactive form. 
